Project name: E-commerce Analytics Simulator

The E-commerce Analytics Simulator is a command-line tool
that helps analyze website activity and customer behavior using event data stored in a CSV file. 
The goal of this project is to demonstrate 
practical data processing, filtering, and KPI calculation using Python.
Loads analytics data from a CSV file

Features: 
- Lets the user filter the data directly in the terminal:
   - by date or date range
   - by user_id
   - by order_id
- Shows a preview of the filtered dataset
- Calculates key performance metrics such as:
   - Total sessions & users
   - Total orders & revenue
   - Conversion rate
   - Average Order Value (AOV)
   - Average number of pages per session
   - Average number of sessions per user
